  East (Kolkata): Chatterjee, Banerjee, Das, Ghosh, Bose…
  Bhopal/MP: Mishra, Dubey, Tiwari, Saxena…
Match region to city. Names must be culturally plausible for the city.

### persona.py  — parameter space

```python
JOB_TYPES = [
    "private_tech",          # EPF yes, NPS no, pension no
    "private_non_tech",      # EPF yes, NPS no, pension no
    "psu_post2004",          # EPF yes, NPS yes, pension no
    "psu_pre2004",           # EPF yes, NPS no, pension YES (old defined-benefit)
    "doctor",                # EPF usually no (private hospital), NPS no
    "lawyer",                # EPF no, NPS no, self-invested
    "ca",                    # EPF no, NPS no, self-invested
    "banker",                # EPF yes, NPS no (private banks)
    "teacher_private",       # EPF yes, NPS no
    "self_employed",         # EPF no, NPS no — heavier own SIP allocation
]

CITIES = [
    "Mumbai", "Delhi", "Bengaluru", "Hyderabad", "Pune",
    "Chennai", "Kolkata", "Ahmedabad", "Jaipur", "Lucknow",
    "Chandigarh", "Bhopal", "Indore", "Kochi",
]

PARAMETER_RANGES = {
    "age":               range(35, 51),           # 35–50
    "monthly_ctc":       range(60_000, 5_00_001, 5_000),  # ₹60K–₹5L
    "existing_savings":  range(0, 20_00_001, 50_000),     # ₹0–₹20L
    "years_experience":  range(5, 26),            # 5–25
}

# monthly_expenses: sample 40–70% of computed take_home
# Call calculate/take_home.py to get take_home first, then sample expense ratio
```

Raise `PersonaExhaustedError` when all unique combinations exhausted.
Call `deduplicator.check(persona)` before returning — raises if duplicate.

### deduplicator.py  — two-layer check

```python
def check(persona: PersonaData, db: Session) -> None:
    h = persona_hash(persona)

    # Layer 1: exact SHA-256 hash
    if db.query(ContentRecord).filter_by(persona_hash=h).first():
        raise PersonaExhaustedError(f"Exact duplicate: {h[:8]}")

    # Layer 2: weighted similarity against recent 500 records
    recent = db.query(ContentRecord).order_by(desc("created_at")).limit(500).all()
    for r in recent:
        prev = PersonaData(**json.loads(r.persona_json))
        if similarity(persona, prev) >= settings.NEAR_DUPLICATE_THRESHOLD:
            raise PersonaNearDuplicateError(
                f"Near-duplicate (score ≥ {settings.NEAR_DUPLICATE_THRESHOLD})"
            )
```

Never set threshold below 0.80 — would allow near-identical videos through.
Default 0.85 in .env. Raise to 0.90 if fires too aggressively.

